    "Alternatively, diffusion has also been used for object detection.",
    "Chen et al. (2023) propose DiffusionDet, a novel approach that iteratively refines detection boxes from initial noise towards precise and accurate localization.",
    "This process involves an initial diffusion phase where ground truth boxes are noised, followed by a reverse process during inference to refine detection.",
    "Such a technique, applied to paleontological imagery, could iteratively detect subcomponents of fossils in 3D scans (e.g., CT), thus providing a novel avenue for DL application in paleontology.",
